<!-- Q1 -->
<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Sequences - limsup of a_n = (-1)^n(1+1/n)</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>For the sequence \(a_n = (-1)^n\!\left(1+\dfrac{1}{n}\right)\), which statement is TRUE?</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (C) \(\limsup a_n = 1\) and \(\liminf a_n = -1\)</strong></p><p>Even terms: \(a_{2k}=1+\frac{1}{2k}\to1^+\), so \(\limsup=1\). Odd terms: \(a_{2k-1}=-(1+\frac{1}{2k-1})\to-1^-\), so \(\liminf=-1\). Since \(\limsup\neq\liminf\), the sequence diverges.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[The sequence converges to 0]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(\limsup a_n = \liminf a_n = 0\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(\limsup a_n = 1\) and \(\liminf a_n = -1\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[\(\limsup a_n = -1\) and \(\liminf a_n = 1\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>

<!-- Q2 -->
<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Sequences - Floor Function Sequence</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Let \(a_n = \dfrac{\lfloor n/2 \rfloor}{n}\). Then \(\displaystyle\lim_{n\to\infty}a_n\) equals:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) \(1/2\)</strong></p><p>For even \(n=2k\): \(a_{2k}=\frac{k}{2k}=\frac{1}{2}\). For odd \(n=2k+1\): \(a_{2k+1}=\frac{k}{2k+1}\to\frac{1}{2}\). Both subsequences tend to \(\frac{1}{2}\), so \(\lim a_n = \frac{1}{2}\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
  <defaultgrade>1.0</defaultgrade><penalty>0.25</penalty><hidden>0</hidden>
  <single>true</single><shuffleanswers>true</shuffleanswers><answernumbering>abc</answernumbering>
