<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Sequences - Monotone Increasing Bounded</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>A sequence \(\{a_n\}\) is monotonically increasing and bounded above. Then:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) It converges to \(\sup\{a_n\}\)</strong></p><p>Monotone Convergence Theorem: a monotone bounded sequence in \(\mathbb{R}\) converges. If increasing and bounded above, it converges to the supremum of its range. This is equivalent to the completeness of \(\mathbb{R}\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
