<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Sequences - Limit of n^(1/n)</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>The value of \(\displaystyle\lim_{n\to\infty} n^{1/n}\) is:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (C) \(1\)</strong></p><p>Let \(a_n=n^{1/n}\). Then \(\ln a_n=\frac{\ln n}{n}\to0\) (since \(\ln n\) grows much slower than \(n\)). So \(a_n=e^{\ln a_n}\to e^0=1\). This limit appears in the Cauchy–Hadamard formula for radius of convergence.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
