<!-- Q14 -->
<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Sequences - Limit of (1+r/n)^n</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>For a fixed real number \(r\), the sequence \(a_n = \left(1+\dfrac{r}{n}\right)^n\) converges to:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (D) \(e^r\)</strong></p><p>\(\ln a_n = n\ln(1+r/n) = n\cdot\left[\frac{r}{n}-\frac{r^2}{2n^2}+O(n^{-3})\right]\to r\). So \(a_n\to e^r\). For \(r=1\) this gives the classical limit \((1+1/n)^n\to e\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
