<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Sequences - CSIR Style limsup/liminf</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>Let \(a_n = \dfrac{(-1)^n n + 1}{n+2}\). Then \(\limsup_{n\to\infty} a_n =\):</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (B) \(1\)</strong></p><p>Even \(n=2k\): \(a_{2k}=\frac{2k+1}{2k+2}\to1\). Odd \(n=2k+1\): \(a_{2k+1}=\frac{-(2k+1)+1}{(2k+1)+2}=\frac{-2k}{2k+3}\to-1\). Cluster points: \(\{1,-1\}\). So \(\limsup=1\).</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
