<!-- Q16 -->
<question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Sequences - Subsequence of a Convergent Sequence</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>If \(a_n\to L\), then every subsequence \(\{a_{n_k}\}\) satisfies:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (A) \(a_{n_k}\to L\)</strong></p><p>Every subsequence of a convergent sequence converges to the same limit. This is because for \(k>N\), \(n_k\geq k>N\), so \(|a_{n_k}-L|<\epsilon\). The converse fails: \(a_n=(-1)^n\) has subsequences converging to \(\pm1\), so the sequence diverges.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
